content.contentDesc:
M: I have three friends. They are Mr Smith, Mrs King and Mr Ben. Each of them has an animal. They like them very much.

Mr Smith has a dog. Its name is Park. Park is kind of shy. It comes from Japan. Mrs King has a young cat. It comes from South Africa. Its name is Run. It is lazy but interesting. Mr Ben has a koala. Its name is Luck. Luck is fun and cute. It comes from Australia.

analysisList.text:
此题考查的是情景对话。第一空根据 I’m going to the South Train Station. 可知问的是去哪；第二空根据 No. It’s the first time for me to take the subway. 可知上句问的是是不是乘地铁；第三空通过答语可知是问的时间2号线什么时候开通的；第四空通过答语是问怎样得到车票；第五空通过下一句话是说非常舒服。

因此，正确答案是第一空Where are you going? 第二空Have you ever taken the subway? 第三空When did Subway Line 2 begin to run? 第四空How can I get the ticket? 第五空It's convenient.

description: 听两遍短文，然后根据所听内容和提示将所缺信息填写在相应位置上。你有1分钟的时间浏览提示信息。（听完录音后，请在90秒钟内将所缺信息输入到指定的答题区域。）

content.contentDesc:
Good morning, everyone. Welcome to People Park. First, you can take a free open-air bus to Animal Corner, our small and special zoo. Take a horse ride and enjoy the cute monkeys. This part of the park is right for all the family.

Leave Animal Corner and walk to your right. Here you will find the Summer Palace. Climb the towers to see a view of the park. When you have finished in the palace, you can go to the West, the street of a 19th century American town. Go into the bank, hotel and doctor's office. The restaurant has real food, and you can enjoy a hamburger before moving on. At 12 noon every day you can watch an exciting show in the street. Next stop is Lake Experience where you can go on a boat. Go on to the final stop, there is the Market of the East, a wonderful place to buy presents for all your friends.

Then the bus will return you back at 4 pm.

analysisList.text:
I was on vacation with my family last week. We went to Penang in Malaysia. We arrived there on Monday morning. It was sunny and hot that day, so we went to the beach near our hotel. My sister and I tried paragliding. We had delicious Malaysian yellow noodles for lunch. We also rode bicycles to Georgetown that afternoon. It was so exciting!

But the next day was very different. My father and I decided to go to Penang Hill and wanted to walk up to the top, but then it started raining a little so we decided to take the train. When we got to the top, it was raining really hard. We were all wet and cold because we had no umbrellas. We couldn’t see anything below because of the bad weather. Without bringing enough money, we only had one bowl of rice and some fish for lunch. Luckily, the food tasted great.
